  "prompt": "What is actually The American Dream?",
  "response": "The American Dream is a national ethos of the United States, characterized by the idea that success is achievable for anyone through hard work, determination, and initiative. It is often associated with the belief in equality of opportunity, meaning that regardless of one's background, everyone has a fair chance to achieve their goals and create a better life for themselves and their families.\n\nHistorically, the American Dream has included the pursuit of prosperity, upward social mobility, and personal freedom. It has been symbolized by home ownership, stable employment, education, and the ability to live a fulfilling life with one's loved ones.\n\nHowever, interpretations of the American Dream can vary widely among individuals, and it has been the subject of much debate and criticism. Some argue that structural inequalities and economic barriers challenge the attainability of the American Dream for many people, while others believe it remains a guiding principle and aspirational goal.\n\nUltimately, the American Dream represents an ideal that has evolved over time but continues to inspire and influence American culture, values, and policy.",
